  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (faults-physical gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The pump is intended for continuous in vivo deployment across multi-hour perfusion runs; bearing wear, seal degradation, and transient electrical interruptions are documented operational hazards in the clinical environment. The CFD model and all validation experiments assume nominal hardware geometry and boundary conditions throughout; no fault states are represented.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
